<section id="welcome">
  <br />
  <br />
   <hr>
<h1>Welcome to Noodle! </h1>

<p>We're glad you’re part of the Noodle Team! Noodle is an exceptional place to work with exceptional people, and you're here because we're committed to keeping it that way.  </p>

<p>This document contains some of the policies designed to contribute to your wellbeing and keep our operations humming.</p>

<p>Although we intend to continue the policies and practices described in this document, we have the right to modify these contents without notice.</p>

</section>
<section id="employment-status">
<hr />
<h2>EMPLOYMENT STATUS</h2>

<h6>Employment at Will</h6>
<p>
Employment with Noodle is on an “at will” basis, which means that the employment relationship is for no definite duration and may be ended at any time by either you or us without cause or notice.  The content of this document does not constitute the terms of a contract of employment, express or implied, or the guarantee of any benefits. This document should not be construed as a guarantee of continued employment.</p>

<p>If you decide to leave us, we request that you notify your manager in writing at least two weeks in advance.  If that happens, we'll determine whether you should continue working once your resignation notice has been received, but pay you through the two weeks regardless. </p>

<h6>Pay When Leaving Noodle</h6>

<ul>
<li>We will pay you through your last day worked</li>
<li>You will be paid for unused paid time off in accordance with Noodle policy</li>
<li>For all pay and benefits purposes, you are considered to have terminated on your employment as of the last day worked. Medical, dental and vision benefits will terminate on the last day of the month in which you have terminated employment</li>
<li>We may make deductions from your final paycheck as compensation for Company property that you don't return at or before termination in accordance with applicable federal and state laws</li>
<li>You generally can't use PTO leave for the notice period</li>
</ul>

<p>If you leave Noodle Education, Inc., you will be entitled to continue health and dental insurance coverage through COBRA.  Employees electing continuation coverage will be responsible for paying the entire premium cost for this coverage.  Employees eligible for COBRA will be provided the necessary paperwork for continuation coverage after their employment terminates.  </p>

</section>
<section id="confidentiality">
<hr />
<h2>CONFIDENTIALITY</h2>

<h6>Work Product</h6>
<p>
All work produced by an employee for Noodle Education, Inc. is the property of Noodle Education, Inc.  This includes, for example, all documents and computer files prepared in connection with Noodle Education, Inc. business, on Noodle Education, Inc. premises, or during paid working hours.  Any appropriation of Noodle Education, Inc. computer files or other employee work product without proper authorization may result in immediate termination and appropriate legal action.</p>

<h6>Confidentiality of Company Affairs</h6>
<p>
Keep all company matters confidential. Be careful or what your reveal about the company inside and outside the office. Noodle employees are exposed to a wide range of confidential and proprietary information. All employees sign a Confidential Agreement before beginning their employment with Noodle.  Any outside requests for information must be approved by the appropriate manager, and all media requests should be directed to Adam Shapiro. Any inquiries from lawyers or government agencies should be directed to Rob Ryman.</p>
<h6>Outside Employment</h6>
<p>
You’re going to be busy contributing to Noodle, and we don’t think it’s a good idea to take other jobs outside your regular work hours. If you’re considering outside work, you need your manager’s approval. Any outside work cannot in any way impact your work at Noodle, compete with Noodle, or involve use of Noodle's time, resources, facilities, or equipment. </p>
</section>
<section id="workplace-environment">
<hr />
<h2>WORKPLACE ENVIRONMENT</h2>
<h6>Policy Against Workplace Harassment</h6>
<p>
Noodle Education, Inc. is committed to maintaining a productive and positive work environment in which all individuals are treated with mutual respect and dignity. We all must contribute to a professional atmosphere that is free of harassment and inappropriate conduct of any form. We cannot tolerate insulting, exploitative, or discriminatory treatment behavior or attitudes. </p>

<p>If you believe you have been harassed, promptly and directly tell the offender that the behavior in question is inappropriate and request that the behavior be stopped or tell a direct supervisor. If an employee believes he or she has witnessed prohibited harassment or other inappropriate behavior, the employee must also notify a member of the Senior Team. Anyone who becomes aware of unlawful discrimination or harassment of any kind is obligated to report it promptly.</p>

<p>Noodle will investigate every complaint and resolve any instance of harassment or discrimination. Each person making a complaint, the alleged harasser/discriminator, and all knowledgeable employees have an obligation to cooperate fully with an investigation. We will maintain confidentiality throughout the investigation to the extent practical and appropriate under the circumstances, considering the sensitive interests of all concerned.  Any person found to have committed prohibited discrimination, harassment or retaliation will be subjected to disciplinary action, including termination.</p>

<p>False, malicious complaints of prohibited harassment –as opposed to complaints that, even if erroneous, are made in good faith—may be the subject of appropriate corrective action.</p>
<h6>Workplace Violence</h6>
<p>
Noodle believes that all employees should be able to work in an environment that is free of any and all forms of workplace violence.  This includes threats and verbal attacks of words, gestures, or display of weapons, which are perceived by an employee as a clear and real threat to the fellow employee’s safety and which may cause anxiety or inability to perform job duties. Noodle will take all reasonable steps to prevent any and all forms of workplace violence from occurring.  As an employer and in the best interests of our employees, it is our obligation to conduct objective, fact-finding investigations immediately following allegations of workplace violence and to take effective action, including termination of employment, to stop such activity and to minimize any effects of workplace violence.  The ultimate objective of our investigation is to end the inappropriate activity and take preventative measures to see that it does not occur in the future. All potentially violent incidents should be immediately reported to a member of the management team. Reports of workplace violence will be handled in as confidential manner as possible. No form of retaliation by an employee following a report of workplace violence will be tolerated.  </p>

<h6>Smoke Free Workplace</h6>
<p> 
Smoking is prohibited inside all Noodle facilities, both for employees and our visitors. </p>

<h6>Substance Abuse</h6>
<p> 
Noodle maintains a drug-free workplace. You may not misuse controlled substances, intoxicants, alcohol and prescription drugs, or buy, sell, manufacture, distribute, possess or work under the influence of illegal substances when conducting Noodle business. If we suspect that you are under the influence of alcohol or an illegal, non-prescribed or other controlled substance, then we may require you to submit to drug or alcohol testing or other medical evaluation. </p>

<p>That said, if you or someone in our family is struggling with a substance abuse issue, we want to help. </p>

<ul>
<li>Contact your manager if you are aware of or have suspicions that a co-worker is misusing controlled substances, intoxicants, alcohol, or prescription drugs or buying, selling, manufacturing, distributing, possessing or working under the influence of illegal substances.</li>
<li>Cooperate fully with management if you are involved in a substance abuse investigation. </li>
</ul>

<h6>Office Hours</h6>
<p>The Noodle workday takes place Monday through Friday with a flexible start-time at 9:00 a.m. Check with your manager regarding what schedule makes the most sense given your responsibilities and the team's goals. If you’re going to be absent or late, inform your manager as early as possible.</p>

<h6>Dress Code</h6> 
<p>Noodle strives to provide a work environment that is both appropriate and comfortable. Our policy permits both casual and formal, but not inappropriate attire. From flip flops and t-shirts to jacket and ties, Noodlers dress for the occasion, and we expect you to use your judgment based on the circumstances. Noodle reserves the right to determine whether an employee’s dress and appearance is appropriate for the workplace.</p>

<p>Media Usage
Don’t misuse or abuse the internet, email, chat, or telephone system while at work or when representing the company. The use of these systems for non-work-related matters should be kept to a minimum and never involve inappropriate or potentially offensive language and images.</p>

<p>Jerk-Free Workplace
We work hard to create an open and fun culture here. Lots of companies say they don't tolerate jerks, but, in practice, they do. <br />
Let's talk about the kind of people who aren't jerks.</p>

<ul>
<li>People who keep their promises. If they say a project will be done by a certain date, they will do everything in their power to make that happen.</li>
<li>People who ask for help. If it can't get done by the promised date, they speak up about the problem and ask for help to make that goal.</li>
<li>People who watch each others' backs. If someone is struggling to get something done, they say, "Hey, can I do anything to help?" whether or not it fits their job description.</li>
<li>People who don't gossip, backstab ,or subvert each other.</li>
</ul>

<p>Jerks propagate quickly in an organization. So when you're hiring someone, don't trade off competence for character—we need people with both.</p>
</section>
