<h2>WORKERS COMPENSATION</h2>

<ul>
<li>Noodle pays all costs of providing workers’ compensation insurance, which may benefit you if you become injured or ill as a result of your work. Workers’ compensation laws vary from state to state. Noodle’s insurance carrier will assist in determining eligibility for benefits and job return provisions.  </li>
<li>In order for Noodle to pay for the cost of treatment, you must be treated by a doctor on the posted Workers’ Compensation procedure Notice.  You will be provided transportation, if needed.</li>
<li>Noodle will work with its workers' compensation insurance carrier in the investigation of any suspected fraudulent workers' compensation claims. Noodle will prosecute any employee who has filed a fraudulent claim or has engaged in other workers' compensation fraud.

Business Travel Policies</li>
</ul>

<p>When traveling for business, employees are eligible to receive meal and per diem allowances according to the schedule below.</p>

<p>Breakfast: $10 (Departure from home before 8 a.m.)
Lunch: $15
Dinner: $25 (Arrival to home after 7 p.m.)
Per Diem: $20 (Applicable for overnight trips or trips during which the employee is eligible for two or more meal allowances.)</p>

<p>Meal allowances will not apply if the employee takes part in a meal a paid for by Noodle.</p>

<p>Employees do not need to submit meal receipts, but must complete and submit a Business Travel Report.  </p>

<p>Airfare, ground transportation fees, and other approved expenses will be reimbursed with the submission of receipts. Employees must make an effort to utilize reasonably-priced transportation options. </p>
</section>
